<br>
<br>
1. balance realms first-pick a path stick to it. either equal opposing classes,which requires cookie cutter approach.  or you balance based on areas of specality.<br>
<br>
2. you can then balance classes based on #1. any attempts at balancng classes without making sure the realms balance out is just an effort in futility,which results only in more problems for mythic to overcome.<br>
<br>
now,people wont like this,because personally i think the best way to balance realms,and avoid the standardized template for all classes across realms,is to specalize. this was/should still be mythics intent. the problem is mythic has failed in that.<br>
<br>
you can talk about balancing the rogue classes among the realms till your blue in the face,but it wont really solve anything,or make this game any better in the long term,unless you figure out how to balance the realms. when you have armsmen who are better then every midgard tank then you have serious issues when trying to say midgard is the meelee realm.<br>
<br>
for me personally i think that shadowblades should be hands down the best meelee rogue in the game,nightshades should be masters of rogue style magic,and infiltrators should be the best all around rogue in the game. i think this pattern should be repeated with all classes in there repsective realms. unfortutnely its far to late to make the kind of drastic changes this would take,so its rather doubtful it will happen.<br>
<br>
as much as you wish to argue against the facts that rogues should be equal,you cant have equality amongst classes,if you cant create equality amongst realms.<br>
<br>
