In any case, I was not suggesting that sbs get 2.5.  I don't think that would be fair.  The differences between the classes don't seem so big now.I would suggest giving sbs enough to raise a mid 30s skill to 39.  That would be something like .1 more I think. That is of course if they don't look at another way to fix it.<br>
<br>
I also disagree on the way you are defining 2h ability as a benefit or a liability.  I don't view it as a liability.  I also don't see it as beneficial at all.<br>
<br>
I think it depends on your spec.  In a five spec you just can't flesh out the spec enough to support the delay in the second hit and thus you just can't open up with a 2hander.  I am sure that you can do just fine as a critblade.  I even watched one do quite well.  However, as soon as the one hit stealth &quot;bug&quot; was removed, I stopped doing 2hander hits.<br>
<br>
The way I view it it's a spec choice in mid at this point.  Just as it is in alb(thrust or slash).  Either you spec high enough to use the 2 hander or you go left axe.  As a result I think the ability to switch is not really a benefit or a liability.  If you want to classify it as a benefit for left axe sbs it is clearly a very small benefit to fit very specific circumstances.  However, I can't think of a time when I would open with a 2 hander. <br>
<br>
I think you are correct to say it's not a liability because that would imply it worked against you.  However, it's not entirely accurate to say it's beneficial, because that suggests it helps you.  The sbs who are upset are 5 spec or true szs like Mill.<br>
<br>
In any case, I apologize for misreading your post.  You did include it. I just missed it.<br>
